(13, 'How does technology influence modern education?', 29, 300, 1, 5, 32, 'Technology has significantly transformed modern education by enhancing accessibility, engagement, and personalized learning. With the rise of digital tools, students and educators now have access to vast resources beyond traditional textbooks. Online platforms, such as Google Classroom and Khan Academy, provide interactive lessons, making learning more engaging and self-paced. Additionally, video conferencing tools like Zoom and Microsoft Teams have enabled remote learning, ensuring education continues despite geographical or pandemic-related barriers.\r\n\r\nMoreover, artificial intelligence (AI) and adaptive learning software analyze student performance and tailor educational content to their individual needs. This personalization helps learners grasp concepts at their own pace, reducing gaps in understanding. Technology has also fostered collaboration through cloud-based tools, allowing students to work on projects in real time, regardless of their location.\r\n\r\nDespite its advantages, technology in education also presents challenges, such as digital divide issues, where students without internet access struggle to keep up. Additionally, excessive screen time can lead to distractions and reduced face-to-face interactions. However, when used effectively, technology enhances learning experiences, making education more inclusive, interactive, and efficient in the modern world.', NULL, NULL, 16),
(13, 'How did Rizal spark the Philippine rebellion?', 29, 300, 2, 5, 32, 'Jos Rizal played a crucial role in sparking the Philippine rebellion against Spanish rule through his writings, reformist ideals, and advocacy for Filipino rights. Although he did not directly lead an armed revolution, his literary works, particularly Noli Me Tangere and El Filibusterismo, exposed the abuses of Spanish friars and officials. These novels awakened the national consciousness of Filipinos, inspiring them to fight for freedom and justice.', NULL, NULL, 17),
